**Segments**

- Technology: The 3D display market can be segmented based on technology into stereoscopic, volumetric, and holographic displays. Stereoscopic displays are the most common type, creating an illusion of depth by presenting two offset images separately to each eye. Volumetric displays create images in three dimensions within a volume of space. Holographic displays use light diffraction to create a virtual three-dimensional image.

- Type: The market can also be segmented based on type into television, smartphone, monitor, HMD, and others. 3D displays are increasingly being incorporated into televisions and smartphones to offer an immersive viewing experience. Monitors with 3D capabilities are utilized in gaming, design, and medical imaging applications. Head-mounted displays (HMDs) are used in virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR) applications.

- Application: The 3D display market can further be segmented based on application into consumer electronics, automotive, healthcare, aerospace and defense, and others. In consumer electronics, 3D displays enhance the user experience in televisions, smartphones, tablets, and gaming consoles. Automotive companies use 3D displays for navigation, entertainment, and driver assistance systems. Healthcare applications include 3D medical imaging for surgeries and diagnostics. Aerospace and defense utilize 3D displays for simulation, training, and situational awareness.

